Question: How to make my image visible by time counter?: :I want to make simple animation using multi-images on android studioi have 3 images (img1,img2,img3)and i want img1 visible firstly then after half second img1 invisible and img2 visible,then after half second img2 invisible and img3 visible,then after half second img3 invisible and img1 visible, so return to the first image like circle 1>2>3>1>2>3>1>2>3 to unlimited time, so how can i do that, please
Please using this api: Activity.findViewById.
Answer:<<<api>>>: Activity.findViewById
<<<code>>>:
private ImageView img1,img2,img3;
private int currentImage = 0;
private ImageView[] images = new ImageView[3];

@Override
protected void onCreate(Bundle savedInstanceState) {
    super.onCreate(savedInstanceState);
    setContentView(R.layout.activity_main);

    img1 = (ImageView) findViewById(R.id.img1);
    img2 = (ImageView) findViewById(R.id.img2);
    img3 = (ImageView) findViewById(R.id.img3);

    images[0] = img1;
    images[1] = img2;
    images[2] = img3;

    for (ImageView image : images) {
        image.setVisibility(View.INVISIBLE);
    }

    images[currentImage].setVisibility(View.VISIBLE);

    new Handler().postDelayed(new Runnable() {
        @Override
        public void run() {
            images[currentImage].setVisibility(View.INVISIBLE);
            currentImage = (currentImage + 1) % images.length;
            images[currentImage].setVisibility(View.VISIBLE);
            new Handler().postDelayed(this, 500);
        }
    }, 500);
}
<<<explanation>>>: This code will make the images visible by a time counter. It uses a Handler to change the visibility of the images every half second. The current image is determined by the currentImage variable, which is incremented and reset to 0 when it reaches the end of the array.

A: You can use the postDelayed method of the Handler class to delay the execution of a certain piece of code.
Here is an example:
new Handler().postDelayed(new Runnable() {
    @Override
    public void run() {
        // Your code here
    }
}, 1000); // Delay in milliseconds

In your case, you can use it to change the background of your button:
new Handler().postDelayed(new Runnable() {
    @Override
    public void run() {
        thisbutton.setBackgroundResource(R.drawable.defaultcard);
    }
}, 1000); // Delay in milliseconds

This will make the button's background change to defaultcard after 1 second.

